#Text=Wikinews interviews Spanish Paralympic swimmer María Delgado
#Text=Wikinews interviews María Delgado .
#Text=Image : Laura Hale .
#Text=María Delgado at Madrid – Barajas Airport Thursday .
#Text=Image : Laura Hale .
#Text=Saturday , August 10 , 2013

#Text=Thursday at Madrid – Barajas Airport , Wikinews interviewed Spanish Paralympic swimmer María Delgado , who is scheduled to compete at the 2013 IPC Swimming World Championships that start on Monday in Montreal , Canada .
#Text=Delgado will be 15 when she is to compete in Montreal .

#Text=I 'm Laura Hale , I 'm interviewing María Delgado who is a Spanish swimmer and who is going to the 2013 IPC Swimming World Championships in Montreal , and you have received a lot of press attention from the Spanish press for being the next great Spanish Swimmer , [ ... ]
#Text=[ Do you expect to medal in this tournament or in Río ? ]
#Text=Spanish language :
#Text=‍¿Crees que en este campeonato vas a ganar una medalla o futuro a Río ?
#Text=[ Note : The translated question here differed from the one originally asked in English . ]
#Text=María Delgado : [ laughs ]
#Text=I do n't know .
#Text=Spanish language : ‍Yo qué sé jajaja .
#Text=The Spanish newspapers say she is the greatest swimmer , she is the next greatest Spanish Paralympic swimmer .
#Text=Does she feel pressure from the media saying that she is a great swimmer to perform in a really high level ?
#Text=Does she feel pressure to win because the newspapers say it ?
#Text=Spanish newspapers say she is the next great Spanish Paralympic swimmer , that she is going to go to Río .

#Text=She has also been future with " plan AXA " , who bet on young swimmers Paralympics , and has been going at concentrations , which are younger with future have driven a little to fit in the world level of competition .

#Text=Spanish language : ‍ ¿ si tienes algún [ here I 'd say : " alguna presión porque " ] ... como que eres el futuro porque eres nueva nadadora , si has salido por ejemplo en el periódico en tu pueblo ?

#Text=Bueno , ella ha sido una apuesta también de un plan que hay de AXA , que apuestan por los jóvenes nadadores paralímpicos , y ha estado yendo a concentraciones , a los que son más jovenes con futuro los han impulsado un poquito para que entren en el mundo de la competición a nivel .
#Text=I 'm on a plan for young talent , that is preparing for Rio 2016 and has selected us , and now we go to the World Championship .
#Text=Spanish language :
#Text=‍Estoy en un plan que es de jóvenes promesas , que nos preparan para Río 2016 y ha apostado por nosotros , y ahora vamos al campeonato del mundo .
#Text=Because you are 15 , how do you [ ... ] balance going to school and competing ?
#Text=It 's a little difficult but with hard work and effort it 's doable .
#Text=Study in the morning and train in the afternoon .
#Text=Spanish language : ‍Es un poco difícil pero con trabajo y esfuerzo se puede conseguir .
#Text=Estudio por la mañana y entreno por la tarde .
#Text=Are you doing school work while you are in Montreal ?
#Text=How does you balance school ?
#Text=How do you do the school at the 15 years old and swim ?
#Text=Because that seems really hard to do both at once .
#Text=Spanish language :
#Text=‍¿Estás haciendo las tareas escolares mientras se encuentra en Montreal ? ¿
#Text=De qué manera a equilibrar la escuela ?
#Text=¿ Cómo se hace la escuela a los 15 años de edad y nadar ?
#Text=Debido a que parece muy difícil hacer las dos cosas a la vez .
#Text=¿ Puedes explicar como por ejemplo qué ¿ ? vas a hacerlo todo normal , no ?
#Text=Que ¿ cómo lo compaginas ?
#Text=Que es muy difícil compaginar y entrenar a la vez natación , o sea , nadar y estudiar .
#Text=It is very difficult to combine and train while swimming , with swimming and studying .
#Text=Spanish language :
#Text=‍Sí , es difícil pero se puede cerrar y hay veces que no sé cómo lo hago ...
#Text=estudiando , yo qué sé ...
#Text=Nos explica por ejemplo que en la Universidad pues tienes que ir más ¿ ? ...
#Text=start very new ... que acaba de empezar y todavía no trae ritmo .
#Text=Because you 're 15 do your parents go with you ?
#Text=Are your parents going to Montreal or are you all traveling solo by yourself ?
#Text=With my coaches .
#Text=My parents are n't going .
#Text=Spanish language : ‍Con mis entrenadores .
#Text=Mis padres no van .
#Text=Only with your coach ?
#Text=Spanish language : ‍¿Sólo con su entrenador ?
#Text=Yes .
#Text=Spanish language :
#Text=‍Sí .
#Text=Is it scary to be on your own ?
#Text=Competing against all these 20 year olds and 30 year olds who 've been to Paralympic games , or you just go " I 'm 15 , I can — el Mundo es mío [ the world is mine ] " ?
#Text=Spanish language :
#Text=‍¿Tienes miedo o tú vas con todas las ganas de competir con gente mayor ?
#Text=I 'm not scared and I go eagerly .
#Text=Spanish language : ‍No tengo miedo y voy con muchas ganas .
#Text=Thank you .
#Text=Spanish language : ‍Gracias .
